We%20spoke%20with%20experts%20to%20gather%20the%20best%20moisturizers%20for%20acne-prone%20skin.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Alexis%20Gaskin)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A2%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fbeauty%2Fbest-moisturizers-acne-prone-skin%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22You'll%20soon%20be%20able%20to%20get%20birth%20control%20without%20a%20prescription.%20Here's%20what%20you%20need%20to%20know.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20box%20of%20OPill%2C%20the%20first%20over-the-counter%20birth%20control%20pill%20in%20a%20teal%20package%20with%20blue%2C%20lavender%20and%20pink%20detailing%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64b004759751e3001929f124%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222667%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20FDA%20approved%20an%20over-the-counter%20birth%20control%20pill%2C%20expanding%20access%20to%20contraceptives%20across%20America.%20It%20will%20hit%20store%20shelves%20in%20March.%20%3Cp%3EPerrigo%2FAssociated%20Press%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EOpill%2C%20an%20oral%20contraceptive%2C%20is%20now%20available%20without%20a%20perscription%20in%20the%20US.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EIt%20is%20the%20first%20hormonal%20birth%20control%20available%20for%20retail%20and%20will%20expand%20access.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20pill%20costs%20%2420%20per%20month%20and%20is%20being%20carried%20by%20Amazon%2C%20Walgreens%2C%20CVS%2C%20Target%2C%20and%20Walmart.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EBirth%20control%20is%20about%20to%20be%20available%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbirth-control-pill-now-available-without-prescription-contraceptives-opill-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewithout%20a%20prescription%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20%2420%20a%20month%20online%20or%20at%20your%20local%20pharmacy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOpill%2C%20an%20oral%20contraceptive%2C%20is%20the%20first%20hormonal%20birth%20control%20to%20become%20available%20for%20retail%20in%20the%20US%20%E2%80%94%20and%20will%20hit%20store%20shelves%20in%20the%20coming%20weeks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20pill%20has%20been%20on%20the%20market%20as%20a%20prescription%20birth%20control%20method%20since%20the%201970s%2C%20and%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffda-approves-first-otc-birth-control-pill-in-us-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eapproved%20for%20retail%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20The%20US%20Food%20and%20Drug%20Administration%20in%20July.%20Amazon%2C%20Walgreens%2C%20CVS%2C%20Target%2C%20and%20Walmart%2C%20as%20well%20as%20most%20drugstores%20and%20supermarkets%20will%20carry%20the%20pill.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPerrigo%2C%20Opill's%20manufacturer%2C%20announced%20Monday%20that%20the%20pills%20will%20be%20sold%20for%20a%20recommended%20retail%20price%20of%20%2419.99%20for%20a%20month's%20supply.%20A%20three-month%20supply%20will%20cost%20%2449.99%2C%20and%20people%20can%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fopill.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebuy%20a%20six-month%20supply%20online%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20%2489.99.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20no%20age%20requirement%20for%20purchasing%20the%20pill.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAbout%2065%25%20of%20women%20ages%2015-49%20use%20some%20form%20of%20contraceptive%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.guttmacher.org%2Ffact-sheet%2Fcontraceptive-use-united-states%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eresearch%20from%20The%20Guttmacher%20Institute%20found%3C%2Fa%3E.%20In%20clinical%20trials%2C%20Opill%20was%2098%25%20effective%20at%20preventing%20pregnancy%20in%20people%20who%20used%20it%20as%20their%20primary%20birth%20control%20method%20for%20a%20full%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EPrescription-free%20birth%20control%20will%20expand%20access%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20introduction%20of%20Opill%20to%20family%20planning%20aisles%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.npr.org%2Fsections%2Fhealth-shots%2F2024%2F03%2F04%2F1235404522%2Fopill-over-counter-birth-control-pill-contraceptive-shop%23%3A~%3Atext%3D%2522We%2520have%2520been%2520working%2520on%2Cat%2520Perrigo%252C%2520which%2520manufactures%2520Opill.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewill%20lower%20barriers%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20birth%20control.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAbout%20half%20of%20all%20US%20pregnancies%20between%202015%20and%202019%20were%20unplanned%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.guttmacher.org%2Ffact-sheet%2Funintended-pregnancy-and-abortion-northern-america%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eper%20the%20latest%20available%20data%20by%20The%20Guttmacher%20Institute%3C%2Fa%3E.%20However%2C%20Guttmacher%20researchers%20said%20unplanned%20pregnancy%20rates%20are%20declining%20%E2%80%94%20largely%20because%20of%20growing%20contraceptive%20access.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBirth%20control%20is%20covered%20by%20most%20insurance%20and%20under%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsupreme-court-upholds-affordable-care-act-california-v-texas-2021-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20Affordable%20Care%20Act%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20but%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.kff.org%2Fwomens-health-policy%2Fissue-brief%2Fwomens-sexual-and-reproductive-health-services-key-findings-from-the-2020-kff-womens-health-survey%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EKFF%3C%2Fa%3E%20(formerly%20known%20as%20Kaiser%20Family%20Foundation)%20found%20that%20about%2025%25%20of%20people%20pay%20some%20out-of-pocket%20costs%20because%20their%20preferred%20birth%20control%20method%2C%20prescribing%20provider%2C%20or%20pharmacy%20is%20out-of-network.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20in%20five%20uninsured%20people%20said%20they%20had%20to%20stop%20using%20a%20contraceptive%20method%20in%202022%20because%20they%20couldn't%20afford%20it%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.kff.org%2Fwomens-health-policy%2Freport%2Fcontraception-in-the-united-states-a-closer-look-at-experiences-preferences-and-coverage%2F%23%3A~%3Atext%3DOne%2520in%2520five%2520uninsured%2520females%2Ca%2520barrier%2520to%2520continued%2520use.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaccording%20to%20KFF%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESince%20Opill%20is%20available%20without%20a%20prescription%2C%20people%20will%20no%20longer%20have%20to%20pay%20a%20doctor%20or%20pharmacist%20to%20access%20hormonal%20birth%20control.%20The%20cost%20of%20Opill%20itself%20may%20also%20be%20eligible%20for%20coverage%20under%20flexible%20spending%20or%20health%20savings%20accounts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ffreethepill.org%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFree%20the%20Pill%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20coalition%20focused%20on%20birth%20control%20access%2C%20called%20the%20introduction%20of%20Opill%20to%20stores%20%26quot%3Ba%20landmark%20moment%20for%20public%20health%20nationwide.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20Project%20Director%20Victoria%20Nichols%20said%20the%20%2419.99%20cost%20for%20one%20month's%20supply%20might%20not%20be%20affordable%20for%20low-income%20people%20and%20people%20working%20to%20make%20ends%20meet.%20She%20urged%20policymakers%20to%20make%20sure%20non-prescription%20birth%20control%20is%20covered%20by%20insurance%20and%20assistance%20programs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BDue%20to%20systemic%20inequities%2C%20cost%20can%20mean%20the%20difference%20between%20people%20getting%20effective%20contraception%20or%20going%20without%2C%26quot%3B%20Nichols%20said%20in%20a%20public%20statement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EHow%20does%20Opill%20work%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOpill%20is%20intended%20to%20be%20taken%20once-per-day%2C%20and%20takes%2048%20hours%20from%20the%20first%20dose%20to%20become%20effective.%20Users%20must%20take%20the%20pill%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.plannedparenthood.org%2Flearn%2Fbirth-control%2Fbirth-control-pill%2Fhow-do-i-use-the-birth-control-pill%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eat%20the%20same%20time%3C%2Fa%3E%20every%20day.%3C%2Fp%3