20the%20message%20%26quot%3BMyBodyMyChoice%26quot%3B%20as%20the%20result%20of%20the%20vote%20was%20announced%20on%20a%20giant%20screen.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAbortion%20rights%20are%20more%20widely%20accepted%20in%20France%20than%20in%20the%20United%20States%20and%20many%20other%20countries%2C%20with%20polls%20showing%20around%2080%25%20of%20French%20people%20back%20the%20fact%20that%20abortion%20is%20legal.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe're%20sending%20a%20message%20to%20all%20women%3A%20your%20body%20belongs%20to%20you%20and%20no%20one%20can%20decide%20for%20you%2C%26quot%3B%20Prime%20Minister%20Gabriel%20Attal%20told%20lawmakers%20ahead%20of%20the%20vote.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWomen%20have%20had%20a%20legal%20right%20to%20abortion%20in%20France%20since%20a%201974%20law%20-%20which%20many%20harshly%20criticised%20at%20the%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20U.S.%20Supreme%20Court's%202022%20decision%20to%20reverse%20the%20Roe%20v.%20Wade%20ruling%20that%20recognised%20women's%20constitutional%20right%20to%20abortion%20prompted%20activists%20to%20push%20France%20to%20become%20the%20first%20country%20to%20explicitly%20protect%20the%20right%20in%20its%20basic%20law.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20right%20(to%20abortion)%20has%20retreated%20in%20the%20United%20States.%20And%20so%20nothing%20authorised%20us%20to%20think%20that%20France%20was%20exempt%20from%20this%20risk%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Laura%20Slimani%2C%20from%20the%20Fondation%20des%20Femmes%20rights%20group.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere's%20a%20lot%20of%20emotion%2C%20as%20a%20feminist%20activist%2C%20also%20as%20a%20woman%2C%26quot%3B%20Slimani%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMonday's%20vote%20enshrined%20in%20Article%2034%20of%20the%20French%20constitution%20that%20%26quot%3Bthe%20law%20determines%20the%20conditions%20in%20which%20a%20woman%20has%20the%20guaranteed%20freedom%20to%20have%20recourse%20to%20an%20abortion%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFrance%20is%20at%20the%20forefront%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20the%20head%20of%20the%20lower%20house%20of%20parliament%2C%20Yael%20Braun-Pivet%2C%20from%20French%20President%20Emmanuel%20Macron's%20centrist%20party.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAbortion%20Rights%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20move%20was%20not%20exempt%20from%20criticism.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFar-right%20leader%20Marine%20Le%20Pen%20said%20Macron%20was%20using%20it%20to%20score%20political%20points%2C%20because%20of%20the%20large%20support%20for%20the%20right%20to%20abortion%20in%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20will%20vote%20to%20include%20it%20in%20the%20Constitution%20because%20we%20have%20no%20problem%20with%20that%2C%26quot%3B%20Le%20Pen%20told%20reporters%20ahead%20of%20the%20Versailles%20vote%2C%20while%20adding%20that%20it%20was%20an%20exaggeration%20to%20call%20it%20a%20historic%20step%20because%2C%20she%20said%2C%20%26quot%3Bno%20one%20is%20putting%20the%20right%20to%20abortion%20at%20risk%20in%20France%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPascale%20Moriniere%2C%20the%20president%20of%20the%20Association%20of%20Catholic%20Families%2C%20called%20the%20move%20a%20defeat%20for%20anti-abortion%20campaigners.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20(also)%20a%20defeat%20for%20women%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said%2C%20%26quot%3Band%2C%20of%20course%2C%20for%20all%20the%20children%20who%20cannot%20see%20the%20day.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMoriniere%20said%20there%20was%20no%20need%20to%20add%20the%20right%20to%20abortion%20to%20the%20constitution.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20imported%20a%20debate%20that%20is%20not%20French%2C%20since%20the%20United%20States%20was%20first%20to%20remove%20that%20from%20law%20with%20the%20repeal%20of%20Roe%20v.%20Wade%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BThere%20was%20an%20effect%20of%20panic%20from%20feminist%20movements%2C%20which%20wished%20to%20engrave%20this%20on%20the%20marble%20of%20the%20constitution.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2