ating%20habits%20are%20similar%20to%20ours.%20Furthermore%2C%20most%20of%20them%20believe%20in%20Christianity.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20interview%20was%20published%20on%20March%201%2C%20the%20minister%E2%80%99s%20controversial%20remarks%20came%20to%20the%20attention%20of%20social%20media%20only%20over%20the%20weekend.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAttempting%20to%20control%20the%20damage%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen.mofa.gov.tw%2FNews_Content.aspx%3Fn%3D1328%26s%3D116677%5C%22%3ETaiwan%E2%80%99s%20foreign%20ministry%20issued%20an%20apology%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20Monday%20(Mar%204).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CRecently%2C%20in%20discussions%20with%20relevant%20sectors%20in%20Taiwan%E2%80%99s%20society%2C%20certain%20government%20agencies%20have%20made%20remarks%20that%20were%20not%20entirely%20appropriate.%20This%20has%20led%20to%20criticism%20among%20Taiwan%E2%80%99s%20society%2C%20Indian%20friends%2C%20and%20other%20international%20stakeholders.%20The%20government%20expresses%20sincere%20apologies%20over%20this%20situation.%20It%20will%20earnestly%20review%20its%20actions%20and%20make%20needed%20improvements%20going%20forward%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20the%20statement.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EStating%20that%20Taiwan%20%E2%80%9Ccherishes%E2%80%9D%20India%E2%80%99s%20diversity%20in%20culture%2C%20It%20also%20noted%20that%20Taiwanese%20society%20had%20a%20wide%20array%20of%20views.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20Taiwan%20government%20also%20hopes%20that%20the%20people%20of%20Taiwan%20will%20support%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20efforts%20to%20engage%20with%20the%20world%2C%20further%20advance%20substantive%20interactions%20with%20partners%20in%20the%20Indo-Pacific%20region%2C%20and%20thereby%20bolster%20reciprocal%20and%20mutually%20beneficial%20exchanges%2C%E2%80%9D%20it%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20has%20been%20no%20official%20reaction%20from%20India%E2%80%99s%20Ministry%20of%20External%20Affairs%2C%20till%20now.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Cem%3Efaux%20pas%3C%2Fem%3E%