.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20justices%20unanimously%20reversed%20a%20Dec.%2019%20decision%20by%20Colorado's%20top%20court%20to%20kick%20Trump%20off%20the%20state's%20Republican%20primary%20ballot%20on%20Tuesday%20after%20finding%20that%20the%20US%20Constitution's%2014th%20Amendment%20disqualified%20him%20from%20again%20holding%20public%20office.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETrump%20is%20the%20frontrunner%20for%20the%20Republican%20nomination%20to%20challenge%20Democratic%20President%20Joe%20Biden%20in%20the%20November%205%20US%20election.%20His%20only%20remaining%20rival%20for%20his%20party's%20nomination%20is%20former%20South%20Carolina%20Governor%20Nikki%20Haley.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBIG%20WIN%20FOR%20AMERICA!!!%2C%26quot%3B%20Trump%20wrote%20on%20his%20social%20media%20platform%20immediately%20after%20the%20ruling.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%2014th%20Amendment's%20Section%203%20bars%20from%20office%20any%20%26quot%3Bofficer%20of%20the%20United%20States%26quot%3B%20who%20took%20an%20oath%20%26quot%3Bto%20support%20the%20Constitution%20of%20the%20United%20States%26quot%3B%20and%20then%20%26quot%3Bengaged%20in%20insurrection%20or%20rebellion%20against%20the%20same%2C%20or%20given%20aid%20or%20comfort%20to%20the%20enemies%20thereof.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20conclude%20that%20states%20may%20disqualify%20persons%20holding%20or%20attempting%20to%20hold%20state%20office.%20But%20states%20have%20no%20power%20under%20the%20Constitution%20to%20enforce%20Section%203%20with%20respect%20to%20federal%20offices%2C%20especially%20the%20presidency%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20unsigned%20opinion%20for%20the%20court%20stated.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20justices%20found%20that%20only%20Congress%20can%20enforce%20the%20provision%20against%20federal%20officeholders%20and%20candidates.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETrump%20was%20also%20barred%20from%20the%20ballot%20in%20Maine%20and%20Illinois%20based%20on%20the%2014th%20Amendment%2C%20but%20those%20decisions%20were%20put%20on%20hold%20pending%20the%20Supreme%20Court's%20ruling%20in%20the%20Colorado%20case.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETrump's%20eligibility%20had%20been%20challenged%20in%20court%20by%20a%20group%20of%20six%20voters%20in%20Colorado%20-%20four%20Republicans%20and%20two%20independents%20-%20who%20portrayed%20him%20as%20a%20threat%20to%20American%20democracy%20and%20sought%20to%20hold%20him%20accountable%20for%20the%20Jan.%206%2C%202021%2C%20attack%20on%20the%20US%20Capitol%20by%20his%20supporters.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20plaintiffs%20were%20backed%20by%20Citizens%20for%20Responsibility%20and%20Ethics%20in%20Washington%2C%20a%20liberal%20watchdog%20group.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20ruling%20came%20on%20the%20eve%20of%20Super%20Tuesday%2C%20the%20day%20in%20the%20US%20presidential%20primary%20cycle%20when%20the%20most%20states%20hold%20party%20nominating%20contests.%20As%20lawsuits%20seeking%20to%20disqualify%20Trump%20cropped%20up%20across%20the%20country%2C%20it%20was%20important%20for%20his%20candidacy%20to%20clear%20any%20hurdles%20to%20appear%20on%20the%20ballot%20in%20all%2050%20states.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Supreme%20Court%20resolved%20the%20Colorado%20ballot%20dispute%20speedily%2C%20a%20timeline%20that%20stands%20in%20contrast%20to%20its%20slower%20handling%20of%20Trump's%20bid%20for%20immunity%20from%20criminal%20prosecution%20in%20a%20federal%20case%20in%20which%20he%20faces%20charges%20for%20trying%20to%20overturn%20his%202020%20election%20loss.%20Trump's%20trial%20has%20been%20put%20on%20hold%20awaiting%20the%20outcome%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court's%20decision%20-%20a%20benefit%20for%20him%20as%20he%20campaigns%20against%20Biden.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20Colorado%20dispute%2C%20the%20justices%20agreed%20to%20take%20up%20the%20case%20a%20mere%20two%20days%20after%20Trump%20filed%20his%20appeal%2C%20fast-tracked%20arguments%20and%20issued%20the%20written%20opinion%20in%20just%20over%20two%20months.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20justices%20in%20the%20immunity%20case%20in%20December%20declined%20a%20bid%20to%20speed%20up%20resolution%20of%20the%20matter%20before%20a%20lower%20court%20had%20weighed%20in%2C%20then%20last%20week%20agreed%20to%20take%20up%20the%20matter%20after%20lower%20courts%20had%20ruled%20-%20setting%20arguments%20to%20take%20place%20in%20late%20April%2C%20a%20much%20longer%20timeline.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Supreme%20Court's%206-3%20conservative%20majority%20includes%20three%20Trump%20appointees.%20Not%20since%20ruling%20in%20the%20landmark%20case%20Bush%20v.%20Gore%2C%20which%20handed%20the%20disputed%202000%20US%20election%20to%20Republican%20George%20W.%20Bush%20over%20Democrat%20Al%20Gore%2C%20has%20the%20court%20played%20such%20a%20central%20role%20in%20a%20presidential%20race.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20bid%20to%20prevent%20Congress%20from%20certifying%20Biden's%202020%20election%20victory%2C%20Trump%20supporters%20attacked%20police%2C%20broke%20through%20barricades%20and%20swarmed%20the%20Capitol.%20Trump%20gave%20an%20incendiary%20speech%20to%20supporters%20beforehand%2C%20repeating%20his%20false%20claims%20of%20widespread%20voting%20fraud%20and%20telling%20them%20to%20go%20to%20the%20Capitol%20and%20%26quot%3Bfight%20like%20hell.%26quot%3B%20He%20then%20for%20hours%20rebuffed%20requests%20that%20he%20urge%20the%20mob%20to%20stop.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%2014th%20Amendment%20was%20ratified%20in%20the%20aftermath%20of%20the%20Civil%20War%20of%201861-1865%20in%20which%20seceding%20Southern%20states%20that%20allowed%20the%20practice%20of%20slavery%20rebelled%20against%20the%20US%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20ruling%20against%20Trump%2C%20Colorado's%20top%20court%20cited%20the%20%26quot%3Bgeneral%20atmosphere%20of%20political%20violence%20that%20President%20Trump%20created%26quot%3B%20and%20that%20he%20aided%20%26quot%3Bthe%20insurrectionists'%20common%20unlawful%20purpose%20of%20preventing%20the%20peaceful%20transfer%20of%20power%20in%20this%20country.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Supreme%20Court%20heard%20arguments%20on%20February%208.%20Trump's%20lawyer%20argued%20that%20he%20is%20not%20subject%20to%20the%20disqualification%20language%20because%20a%20president%20is%20not%20an%20%26quot%3Bofficer%20of%20the%20United%20States%2C%26quot%3B%20that%20the%20provision%20cannot%20be%20enforced%20by%20courts%20absent%20congressional%20legislation%2C%20and%20that%20what%20occurred%20on%20Jan.%206%20was%20shameful%2C%20criminal%20and%20violent%20but%20not%20an%20insurrection.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMany%20Republicans%20have%20decried%20the%20ballot%20disqualification%20drive%20as%20election%20interference%2C%20while%20proponents%20of%20disqualification%20have%20said%20holding%20Trump%20constitutionally%20accountable%20for%20an%20insurrection%20supports%20democratic%20values.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1709566080000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-01%2F8l68b4e8_donald-trump-afp_625x300_17_January_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fdonald-trump-wins-colorado-ballot-disqualification-case-at-us-supreme-court-5175839%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22US%20Supreme%20Court%20handed%20Trump%20major%20victory%20on%20Monday%2C%20overturning%20a%20judicial%20decision%20that%20had%20excluded%20him%20from%20Colorado's%20ballot%20under%20a%20constitutional%20provision%20involving%20insurrection%20for%20inciting%20and%20supporting%20January%206%2C%202021%2C%20Capitol%20attack.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fdonald-trump-wins-colorado-ballot-disqualification-case-at-us-supreme-court-5175839%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Sara%20Tendulkar's%20fan%20moment%20with%20Rani%20Mukerji%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22pub