s%20termination%20at%20the%20just-concluded%20World%20Trade%20Organisation%E2%80%99s%20ministerial%20conference%20in%20Abu%20Dhabi%20last%20week.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUnion%20commerce%20minister%20Piyush%20Goyal%20said%20the%20e-commerce%20moratorium%2C%20which%20refrains%20from%20imposing%20customs%20duties%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Ftrade%2Fwtos-ecommerce-moratorium-india-us%5C%22%3Efavoured%3C%2Fa%3E%20big%20tech%20companies%20and%20undermined%20the%20prospects%20of%20competitors%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ft.com%2Fcontent%2F72ddf2e7-f467-473d-8ec2-07f09a7862d9%5C%22%3Edeveloping%3C%2Fa%3E%20countries.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EYet%2C%20on%20the%20final%20day%20of%20the%20conference%2C%20he%20took%20a%20U-turn.%20He%20allowed%20it%20to%20continue%20for%20another%20two%20years%20for%20free%2C%20without%20securing%20a%20tangible%20return.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGoyal%20said%20he%20agreed%20to%20the%20continuation%20of%20the%20e-commerce%20moratorium%20because%20the%20UAE%20trade%20minister%2C%20Dr%20Thani%20bin%20Ahmed%20Al%20Zeoudi%2C%20who%20is%20also%20the%20chair%20of%20the%20ministerial%20conference%2C%20requested%20him%20personally%20to%20do%20so.%20%E2%80%9CHe%20is%20a%20friend%2C%20and%20out%20of%20friendship%2C%20I%20agreed%2C%E2%80%9D%20Goyal%20told%20reporters.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20Indonesia%2C%20one%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20staunchest%20allies%20in%20WTO%E2%80%99s%20farm%20negotiations%2C%20was%20not%20even%20informed%20by%20India%20about%20its%20decision%20to%20drop%20the%20opposition%20to%20e-commerce%20moratorium%2C%20a%20senior%20Indonesian%20official%20told%20this%20reporter.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndonesia%2C%20however%2C%20went%20on%20to%20block%20the%20continuation%20of%20the%20moratorium%20in%20the%20final%20hours%20of%20the%20meeting.%20Finally%2C%20coming%20under%20intense%20pressure%2C%20Indonesia%20relented.%20Had%20India%20remained%20firm%2C%20the%20moratorium%20would%20not%20have%20gone%20through.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIt%E2%80%99s%20a%20relief%20to%20see%20the%20moratorium%20survive%20by%20the%20skin%20of%20its%20teeth%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Tiffany%20Smith%2C%20vice-president%20of%20the%20National%20Foreign%20Trade%20Council%2C%20a%20Washington-based%20business%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ft.com%2Fcontent%2F72ddf2e7-f467-473d-8ec2-07f09a7862d9%5C%22%3Elobby%3C%2Fa%3E%20group.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIts%20collapse%20would%20be%20a%20significant%20blow%20to%20the%20rules-based%20trading%20system.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CBut%20it%E2%80%99s%20incredibly%20frustrating%20to%20see%20the%20WTO%20unable%20to%20move%20forward%20from%20this%20Groundhog%20Day%20rut%20that%20has%20been%20dug%20on%20the%20issue.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20endless%20brinkmanship%20over%20the%20moratorium%20crowds%20out%20the%20ability%20to%20make%20progress%20on%20a%20broader%20agenda%20and%20undermines%20the%20viability%20of%20the%20WTO%20as%20a%20useful%20forum%20for%20trade%20ministers%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20told%3Cem%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ft.com%2Fcontent%2F72ddf2e7-f467-473d-8ec2-07f09a7862d9%5C%22%3EFinancial%20Times%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%E2%80%99s%20stand%20on%20moratorium%2C%20which%20had%20been%20in%20place%20since%201998%20with%20tens%20of%20billions%20of%20dollars%20in%20foregone%20customs%20revenues%20for%20developing%20countries%2C%20is%20somewhat%20perplexing.%20Is%20it%20a%20reciprocal%20gesture%20for%20the%20temple%20that%20was%20built%20in%20Abu%20Dhabi%20recently%3F%20Nobody%20would%20know.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECuriously%2C%20it%20came%20days%20after%20a%20new%20temple%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Fmodi-inaugurates-baps-temple-in-uae%5C%22%3Ewas%20inaugurated%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi.%20Even%20the%20commerce%20minister%20who%20came%20late%20to%20the%20meeting%20in%20Abu%20Dhabi%20made%20his%20first%20stop%20at%20the%20temple.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20all%2C%20in%20global%20trade%20negotiations%20conducted%20by%20the%20WTO%2C%20everything%20comes%20with%20what%20is%20called%20in%20the%20negotiating%20parlance%20a%20%E2%80%9Cpayment%E2%80%9D.%20It%20implies%20that%20if%20country%20X%20is%20asking%20country%20Y%20to%20agree%20to%20accept%20its%20demand%2C%20that%20would%20involve%20a%20binding%20commitment%2C%20then%20the%20latter%20has%20to%20make%20a%20commensurate%20payment%2C%20in%20return.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F04174246%2Fimage-1904.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F04174246%2Fimage-1904.png%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F04174246%2Fimage-1904-300x159.png%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F04174246%2Fimage-1904-1024x543.png%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-700087%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22636%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EA%20meeting%20with%20Union%20commerce%20minister%3Cbr%3EPiyush%20Goyal%3Cbr%3Eand%20the%20Indian%20delegation%2C%20focused%20on%20India%E2%80%99s%20priorities%20for%20MC13.%20Photo%3A%20X%40NOIweala%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPublic%20stockholding%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20representatives%20from%20powerful%20American%20lobbies%20present%20at%20the%20meeting%2C%20India%20could%20have%20forced%20the%20US%20administration%20and%20other%20industrialised%20countries%20to%20agree%20to%20the%20permanent%20solution%20for%20public%20stockholding%20programmes%20for%20food%20security.%20This%20is%20a%20mandated%20issue%20hanging%20in%20balance%20since%20the%20WTO%E2%80%99s%2010th%20ministerial%20conference%20in%202015.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20fierce%20opposition%20from%20the%20US%20which%20reckons%20that%20the%20initial%20Bali%20peace%20clause%20agreed%20at%20the%20WTO%E2%80%99s%20ninth%20ministerial%20conference%20in%20Indonesia%20is%20a%20%E2%80%9Cmistake%E2%80%9D%20and%20it%20should%20not%20have%20happened.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThough%20India%20paid%20for%20the%20peace%20clause%20by%20agreeing%20to%20a%20brand%20new%20trade%20facilitation%20agreement%2C%20the%20US%20has%20been%20consistently%20blocking%20the%20permanent%20solution%20for%20public%20stockholding%20programmes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20discussions%20on%20public%20stockholding%20at%20the%20Abu%20Dhabi%20meeting%20were%20pretty%20tense%20and%20replete%20with%20some%20heated%20exchanges.%20For%20example%2C%20at%20the%20meeting%20of%20eight%20countries%2C%20India%20is%20understood%20to%20have%20said%20that%20without%20a%20permanent%20solution%20for%20public%20stockholding%2C%20there%20would%20not%20be%20any%20outcome%20in%20agriculture%20for%20the%20next%20100%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%20also%20subtly%20reminded%20the%20WTO%E2%80%99s%20Director%20General%2C%20Ngozi%20Okonjo-Iweala%2C%20who%20seemingly%20breached%20her%20role%20as%20an%20international%20civil%20servant%20by%20promoting%20the%20controversial%20plurilateral%20agreement%20on%20investment%20facilitation%2C%20a%20core%20priority%20for%20China%2C%20that%20she%20could%20have%20helped%20India%20in%20resolving%20the%20permanent%20solution%20for%20public%20stockholding%20programmes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOkonjo-Iweala%20appears%20to%20have%20said%20it%20is%20not%20for%20her%20to%20negotiate%20on%20public%20stockholding%2C%20suggesting%20that%20it%20is%20for%20India%20to%20negotiate%20with%20other%20members%20to%20resolve%20the%20issue.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20Trade%20Representative%20Ambassador%2C%20Katherine%20Tai%2C%20who%20left%20Abu%20Dhabi%20early%20morning%20on%20Friday%2C%20seems%20to%20have%20opposed%20the%20permanent%20solution%2C%20while%20suggesting%20continuing%20work%20on%20a%20permanent%20solution%20along%20with%20other%20issues%2C%20said%20delegates%20who%20asked%20not%20to%20be%20quoted.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20tough%20stance%20adopted%20by%20India%20on%20the%20public%20stockholding%20issue%2C%20a%20US%20official%20seems%20to%20have%20suggested%20that%20the%20MC-13%20is%20an%20%E2%80%9CIndia%20party%E2%80%9D%2C%20implying%20that%20India%20is%20dominating%20the%20proceedings%20on%20every%20issue%2C%20according%20to%20delegates%20familiar%20with%20the%20discussions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20several%20developing%20countries%20pointed%20fingers%20at%20the%20US%20for%20blocking%20the%20public%20stockholding%20matter%2C%20resulting%20in%20an%20overall%20negative%20impact%20on%20other%20issues%2C%20said%20a%20developing%20country%20delegate%2C%20who%20asked%20not%20to%20be%20quoted.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUltimately%2C%20India%20blocked%20the%20Investment%20Facilitation%20for%20Development%20agreement.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGoyal%20made%20the%20right%20noises%20about%20the%20restoration%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Findia%2Fsatisfied-as-interests-of-indian-farmers-fishermen-protected-at-wto-goyal%2Farticleshow%2F108169261.cms%5C%22%3Eappellate%3C%2Fa%3E%20body%2C%20the%20highest%20limb%20for%20adjudicating%20trade%20disputes.%20The%20appellate%20body%20has%20remained%20dysfunctional%20since%202019%20after%20Washington%20blocked%20the%20selection%20of%20members%20to%20the%20appellate%20body.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EConsequently%2C%20the%20WTO%E2%80%99s%20enforcement%20mechanism%20has%20become%20ineffective%2C%20even%20though%20the%20panel%20process%2C%20serving%20as%20the%20lower%20court%20beneath%20the%20appellate%20body%2C%20remains%20operational.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%20should%20have%20put%20in%20strong%20language%20in%20the%20Abu%20Dhabi%20mandate%20for%20reforming%20the%20broken%20dispute%20settlement%20system.%20In%20light%20of%20this%2C%20there%20seems%20to%20be%20no%20justification%20in%20concluding%20new%20agreements%20at%20the%20WTO.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F04174511%2Fimage-1905.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F04174511%2Fimage-1905.png%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F04174511%2Fimage-1905-300x175.png%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F04174511%2Fimage-1905-1024x598.png%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-700088%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22701%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EThe%2013th%20WTO%20ministerial%20conference%20in%20Abu%20Dhabi.%20Photo%3A%20X%40ThaniAlZeyoudi%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EFisheries%20subsidies%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERegarding%20the%20so-called%20second%20wave%20of%20fisheries%20subsidies%20negotiations%20aimed%20at%20addressing%20subsidies%20that%20contribute%20to%20overcapacity%20and%20overfishing%2C%20the%20final%20text%20presented%20on%20the%20negotiating%20table%20appears%20to%20have%20undermined%20commitments%20to%20curtail%20significant%20subsidies%20responsible%20for%20the%20depletion%20of%20global%20fish%20stocks.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20agreement%20appeared%20devoid%20of%20any%20significance%20with%20tailored%20exemptions%20allowing%20the%20European%20Union%2C%20the%20US%2C%20China%2C%20Japan%2C%20Korea%2C%20and%20Taipei%20to%20continue%20with%20their%20subsidies%20contributing%20to%20overcapacity%20and%20overfishing.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERegrettably%2C%20provisions%20for%20special%20and%20differential%20treatment%20aimed%20at%20aiding%20the%20development%20of%20marine%20sectors%20in%20developing%20countries%20were%20sparse.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%E2%80%99s%20decision%20to%20block%20the%20fisheries%20subsidies%20agreement%20seems%20justified%20in%20this%20context.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOverall%2C%20India%20has%20done%20some%20things%20right%20at%20the%20Abu%20Dhabi%20meeting.%20However%2C%20it%20blundered%20on%20one%20issue%3A%20giving%20up%20on%20the%20termination%20of%20the%20e-commerce%20moratorium.%20It%20is%20a%20jewel%20in%20the%20crown%20for%20the%20US%20and%20other%20industrialised%20countries.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ETense%20exchanges%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBefore%20the%20meeting%20came%20to%20a%20close%2C%20it%20witnessed%20some%20intense%20moments%20marked%20by%20tense%20exchanges%20between%20Okonjo-Iweala%20and%20Goyal.%20He%20seemed%20piqued%20over%20alleged%20attempts%20to%20cast%20India%20in%20a%20bad%20light%20over%20its%20refusal%20to%20agree%20with%20the%20fisheries%20subsidies%20agreement.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGoyal%20apparently%20learned%20from%20Fiji%E2%80%99s%20Deputy%20Prime%20Minister%20and%20Minister%20for%20Trade%2C%20Manoa%20Kamikamica%2C%20that%20he%20is%20issuing%20a%20statement%20on%20fisheries%20subsidies%20after%20India%20blocked%20the%20fisheries%20subsidies%20agreement.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20appears%20that%20the%20Fijian%20minister%20is%20understood%20to%20have%20told%20India%20that%20Okonjo-Iweala%20had%20asked%20him%20to%20issue%20the%20statement%20on%20the%20fisheries%20subsidies%2C%20after%20which%20Goyal%20rushed%20to%20the%20podium%20to%20tell%20her%20about%20what%20he%20heard%20on%20fisheries%20subsidies%20from%20his%20Fijian%20counterpart.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESeemingly%20enraged%20at%20the%20development%2C%20the%20Indian%20minister%20appears%20to%20have%20threatened%20the%20Director-General%20that%20India%20would%20withdraw%20its%20approval%20extended%20to%20the%20e-commerce%20moratorium.%20This%20threat%20stemmed%20from%20allegations%20that%20she%20advised%20the%20Fijian%20deputy%20prime%20minister%20to%20issue%20a%20statement%2C%20despite%20an%20agreement%20that%20there%20will%20be%20no%20statement%20on%20the%20fisheries%20subsidies.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThat%20created%20a%20panic%20and%20a%20visibly%20shaken%20Director-General%20tried%20to%20convince%20Goyal%20that%20she%20did%20not%20tell%20the%20Fijian%20minister.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOkonjo-Iweala%20appears%20to%20have%20challenged%20the%20Fijian%20minister%20whether%20she%20told%20him%20to%20issue%20the%20statement%20on%20the%20fisheries%20subsidies.%20The%20Director-General%20appears%20to%20have%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CPiyush%20you%20know%20me%2C%20why%20would%20I%20do%20that%2C%E2%80%9D%20according%20to%20ministers%20who%20heard%20the%20conversation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20asked%20whether%20the%20Director-General%20put%20up%20Fiji%20to%20issue%20a%20statement%20on%20fisheries%20subsidies%20to%20single%20out%20India%20at%20the%20meeting%20on%20fisheries%20subsidies%2C%20the%20WTO%20spokesperson%20referred%20this%20writer%20to%20check%20with%20the%20Fijian%20deputy%20prime%20minister.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAs%20the%20spokesperson%20for%20the%20WTO%2C%20I%20highly%20recommend%20reaching%20out%20to%20the%20Fijian%20delegation%20for%20exact%20information%20concerning%20any%20statements%20made%20or%20not%20made.%20It%20is%20our%20customary%20practice%20to%20refrain%20from%20addressing%20or%20commenting%20on%20unfounded%20rumours%20or%20hearsay%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Ismail%20Dieng%2C%20WTO%E2%80%99s%20spokesperson.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENevertheless%2C%20the%20tense%20exchange%20between%20the%20Director-General%20and%20the%20Indian%20minister%20seems%20to%20have%20vitiated%20the%20overall%20climate%20during%20the%20MC-13%2C%20said%20ministers%20familiar%20with%20the%20differences%20between%20an%20international%20civil%20servant%20and%20a%20trade%20minister%20of%20a%20sovereign%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1