20so%20that%20land%20allotted%20to%20expand%20the%20district%20judiciary%E2%80%99s%20footprint%20can%20be%20utilised%20on%20an%20expeditious%20basis%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20court%20said%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livelaw.in%2Ftop-stories%2Fvacate-delhi-plot-which-is-meant-for-delhi-judiciary-by-june-15-supreme-court-directs-aap-251188%5C%22%3Eaccording%20to%20%3Cem%3ELivelaw.in%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20court%20also%20asked%20AAP%20to%20approach%20the%20Land%20And%20Development%20Office%20(LDO)%20for%20allotment%20of%20land%20for%20its%20offices.%20It%20asked%20LDO%20to%20process%20the%20party%E2%80%99s%20request%20within%20four%20weeks%2C%20and%20asked%20the%20department%20to%20communicate%20its%20decision%20by%20the%20stipulated%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAAP%20argued%20that%20its%20party%20office%20near%20the%20Rouse%20Avenue%20court%20isn%E2%80%99t%20an%20%E2%80%98encroachment%E2%80%99%20since%20it%20was%20allotted%20long%20before%20it%20was%20allocated%20for%20the%20extension%20of%20the%20court.%20The%20top%20court%20had%2C%20in%20February%2C%20observed%20that%20AAP%20was%20encroaching%20on%20the%20land%2C%20which%20was%20allotted%20to%20the%20Delhi%20high%20court%20for%20an%20expansion%20project%20%E2%80%93%20the%20building%20of%20additional%20courtrooms%20for%20the%20Rouse%20Avenue%20court.%20The%20top%20court%20took%20note%20of%20the%20matter%20while%20dealing%20with%20a%20case%20related%20to%20judicial%20infrastructure%20across%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Bench%20led%20by%20CJI%20Chandrachud%20has%20now%20asked%20AAP%20to%20move%20to%20an%20alternative%20spot%20in%20Delhi%E2%80%99s%20outskirts%20in%20Badarpur%20to%20set%20up%20its%20party%20office.%20In%20response%2C%20AAP%E2%80%99s%20counsel%20Abhishek%20Manu%20Singhvi%20said%20if%20AAP%20is%20asked%20to%20move%20to%20Badarpur%2C%20all%20other%20parties%20must%20also%20do%20the%20same.%20He%20said%20the%20party%20should%20at%20least%20get%20a%20space%20in%2