22title%22%3A%22SC%20strips%20immunity%20in%20bribery%20cases%3A%20What%20it%20means%20for%20MPs%2C%20MLAs%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1709552072000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-108206341%2Cimgsize-932139.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Findia%2Fexplainer-supreme-court-ends-immunity-for-lawmakers-taking-bribes-to-vote-what-does-it-mean%2Farticleshow%2F108204221.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Supreme%20Court%20today%20ruled%20that%20lawmakers%20cannot%20claim%20immunity%20from%20prosecution%20in%20bribery%20cases.%20The%20court%20explained%20that%20the%20legal%20protection%20provided%20to%20MPs%20and%20MLAs%20under%20Articles%20105%20and%20194%20of%20the%20Constitution%20does%20not%20shield%20them%20in%20cases%20of%20accepting%20bribes%20for%20votes%20or%20speeches%20in%20the%20House.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22TOI%20NEWS%20DESK%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Findia%2Fexplainer-supreme-court-ends-immunity-for-lawmakers-taking-bribes-to-vote-what-does-it-mean%2Farticleshow%2F108204221.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Enrolment%20into%20Higher%20Education%20Among%20Muslims%20Falls%2C%20North%20India%20Lags%20Behind%20the%20South%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F02%2F08140805%2FPhoto-4.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20southern%20states%20have%20by%20far%20a%20bigger%20rate%20of%20enrolment%20in%20higher%20education%20of%20students%20from%20Muslim%20communities%20as%20compared%20to%20their%20peers%20in%20other%20parts%20of%20India%20%E2%80%93%20particularly%20Uttar%20Pradesh%2C%20Bihar%2C%20where%20the%20community%E2%80%99s%20population%20is%20significant.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20has%20been%20stated%20in%20a%20study%20titled%20%E2%80%9CState%20of%20Muslim%20Education%20in%20India%E2%80%9D%20compiled%20and%20analysed%20by%20former%20professor%20Arun%20C%20Mehta%2C%20who%20was%20heading%20the%20Educational%20Management%20Information%20System%20(EMIS)%20at%20the%20National%20University%20of%20Educational%20Planning%20%26amp%3B%20Administration%20(NIEPA).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20study%20was%20compiled%20based%20on%20the%202020-21%20and%202021-22%20data%20from%20the%20Unified%20District%20Information%20System%20for%20Education%20Plus%20(UDISE%20Plus)%20%E2%80%93%20the%20largest%20school%20education%20database%20%E2%80%93%20and%20the%202020-21%20data%20from%20the%20All%20India%20Survey%20on%20Higher%20Education%20(AISHE).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20two%20are%20under%20the%20supervision%20of%20the%20Union%20Ministry%20of%20Education.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EMuslim%20education%20in%20southern%20states%2C%20UTs%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFrom%2017%2C39%2C218%20Muslim%20students%20enrolled%20in%20higher%20education%20in%202016-17%20in%20South%20Indian%20states%20and%20Union%20territories%20(UTs)%2C%20the%20number%20increased%20to%2021%2C00%2C860%20students%20in%202019-20.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20there%20was%20a%20decline%20of%208.53%25%20in%20the%20following%20year%2C%20as%20the%20number%20of%20Muslim%20enrolments%20in%20higher%20education%20stood%20at%2019%2C21%2C713%20%E2%80%93%20a%20drop%20of%201%2C79%2C147%20students.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20395px)%2085vw%2C%20395px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F04160709%2FMuslim-Gross-Enrolment-Ratio-in-Higher-Education-in-Southern-and-Hindi-heartland-states-2020-21.jpeg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22395%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F04160709%2FMuslim-Gross-Enrolment-Ratio-in-Higher-Education-in-Southern-and-Hindi-heartland-states-2020-21.jpeg%20770w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F04160709%2FMuslim-Gross-Enrolment-Ratio-in-Higher-Education-in-Southern-and-Hindi-heartland-states-2020-21-246x300.jpeg%20246w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-700059%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22482%5C%22%3EThe%20national%20average%20of%20Muslim%20students%E2%80%99%20Gross%20Enrolment%20Ratio%20(GER)%20between%20the%20age%20group%2018%20and%2023%20was%208.41%25%2C%20with%20women%20performing%20better%20with%20a%20higher%20GER%20of%209.43%25%20and%20males%20(8.44%25).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20GER%20of%20Muslim%20students%20in%20seven%20southern%20states%20%E2%80%93%20Andhra%20Pradesh%2C%20Kerala%2C%20Karnataka%2C%20Tamil%20Nadu%2C%20and%20Telangana%20%E2%80%93%20and%20UTs%20was%20higher%20in%20general.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Telugu%20state%20of%20Telangana%20leads%20the%20pack%20with%20a%20GER%20of%20nearly%2034%25%2C%20followed%20by%20Tamil%20Nadu%2C%20which%20lies%20at%20around%2028%25%2C%20as%20per%20the%20study.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAmong%20the%20states%2C%20next%20on%20the%20list%20is%20Kerala%20%E2%80%93%20the%20literacy%20hub%20of%20India%20%E2%80%93%20where%20a%20total%20of%2020%25%20of%20Muslim%20students%20make%20it%20to%20higher%20studies.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EImpressively%2C%20over%2025%25%20of%20them%20are%20women%20%E2%80%93%20with%20a%20huge%2010%20percentage%20point%20gap%20over%20their%20male%20counterparts.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKerala%20is%20followed%20by%20neighbouring%20Karnataka%2C%20with%2015.78%25%20students%20enrolled%20from%20the%20Muslim%20community.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20study%2C%20the%20other%20Telugu%20state%20of%20Andhra%20Pradesh%20falls%20at%20the%20bottom%20of%20the%20list%20with%20a%20mere%2010%25%20of%20the%20Islamic%20students%20goes%20to%20college.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20per%20the%202011%20census%2C%20the%20state%20had%20a%20Muslim%20population%20share%20of%209.56%25%20in%202011.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20it%20comes%20to%20the%20UTs%20in%20the%20southern%20region%2C%20over%2025%25%20of%20Muslim%20students%20in%20Puducherry%20were%20found%20enrolled%20in%20higher%20studies%20as%20compared%20to%20a%20meagre%20of%20over%204%25%20in%20Lakshadweep%20irrespective%20of%20its%20predominant%20Muslim%20population%20(over%2096%25).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EIn%20Hindi-heartland%20states%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Hindi%20heartland%20comprises%20at%20least%20nine%20states%20and%20a%20UT%20%E2%80%93%20Uttar%20Pradesh%2C%20Bihar%2C%20Madhya%20Pradesh%2C%20Jharkhand%2C%20Himachal%20Pradesh%2C%20Haryana%2C%20Chhattisgarh%2C%20Rajasthan%2C%20Uttarakhand%2C%20and%20Delhi.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20per%20the%20study%2C%20all%20of%20them%20have%20an%20average%20of%20nearly%207%25%20of%20Muslim%20students%20enrolled%20in%20higher%20studies%2C%20which%20is%2012%20percentage%20points%20lower%20than%20their%20southern%20counterparts.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAmong%20them%2C%20Jharkhand%20has%20the%20highest%20share%20of%20Muslim%20students%20receiving%20higher%20education%20(nearly%2015%25)%20followed%20by%20Uttarakhand%20(12.48%25).%20These%20are%20the%20only%20two%20states%20with%20figures%20amounting%20to%20double%20digits%20on%20that%20account.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUttarakhand%20%E2%80%93%20the%20state%20that%20recently%20became%20the%20first%20state%20to%20approve%20the%20Uniform%20Civil%20Code%20(UCC)%20%E2%80%93%20also%20has%20the%20highest%20share%20of%20Muslim%20female%20students%20(over%2013%25)%20enrolled%20in%20college%20among%20the%20Hindi%20heartland%20states.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20third%20in%20the%20overall%20pack%20is%20the%20national%20capital%20Delhi%2C%20with%207.09%25%20of%20students%20from%20the%20Muslim%20community%20enrolled%20in%20college%2C%20with%20Chhattisgarh%20(7%25)%20right%20behind%20it.%20Sitting%20at%206.57%20%25%2C%20Madhya%20Pradesh%20closely%20follows.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENext%20on%20the%20list%20are%20Bihar%2C%20Uttar%20Pradesh%2C%20and%20Rajasthan%2C%20with%206.13%25%2C%205.43%25%2C%20and%205.08%25%20%E2%80%93%20respectively%20%E2%80%93%20of%20students%20taking%20up%20higher%20studies%2C%20at%20least%20till%20graduation%20level.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHaryana%2C%20with%20a%20meagre%204.49%25%2C%20sits%20at%20the%20bottom%20of%20Hindi%20heartland%20states%20where%20Muslim%20students%20made%20it%20to%20higher%20education%20institutes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESharp%20difference%20in%20socio-economic%20indicators%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKM%20Ziyauddin%2C%20a%20professor%20at%20the%20Department%20of%20Sociology%20of%20the%20Maulana%20Azad%20National%20Urdu%20University%20(MANUU)%2C%20noted%20that%20there%20was%20a%20sharp%20difference%20in%20socio-economic%20indicators%20among%20students%20from%20the%20southern%20states%20and%20the%20ones%20belonging%20to%20the%20Hindi%20heartland.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20361px)%2085vw%2C%20361px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F04160817%2FTransition-Rate-of-Muslim-Students-Enrolment-in-School-Education-in-Southern-states-and-Hindi-heartland-states-2021-22.jpeg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22361%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F04160817%2FTransition-Rate-of-Muslim-Students-Enrolment-in-School-Education-in-Southern-states-and-Hindi-heartland-states-2021-22.jpeg%20937w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F04160817%2FTransition-Rate-of-Muslim-Students-Enrolment-in-School-Education-in-Southern-states-and-Hindi-heartland-states-2021-22-234x300.jpeg%20234w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F04160817%2FTransition-Rate-of-Muslim-Students-Enrolment-in-School-Education-in-Southern-states-and-Hindi-heartland-states-2021-22-800x1024.jpeg%20800w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-700061%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22462%5C%22%3E%E2%80%9CBe%20it%20in%20terms%20of%20per-capita%20income%20or%20the%20development%20of%20southern%20states%2C%20the%20southern%20states%20are%20ahead.%20Affirmative%20policies%20by%20the%20state%20%E2%80%93%20like%20reservation%20%E2%80%93%20started%20long%20back%20in%20Karnataka%2C%E2%80%9D%20noted%20Ziyauddin.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20policies%20%E2%80%9Cwere%20introduced%20to%20increase%20student%20enrolment%20of%20the%20marginalised%20and%20backward%20communities%E2%80%9D%2C%20he%20explaind.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIn%20Telangana%2C%20several%20schemes%20%E2%80%93%20like%20KG2PG%20and%20Minority%20Residential%20Welfare%20Schools%20%E2%80%93%20are%20running%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20noted.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EZiyauddin%20added%20that%20the%20aforementioned%20steps%20helped%20increase%20the%20availability%20of%20schools%20and%20institutions%20%E2%80%93%20not%20just%20for%20minorities%20but%20to%20almost%20all%20citizens.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20teaching%20quality%20and%20regular%20monitoring%20are%20also%20comparatively%20better%2C%20as%20we%20found%20in%20several%20studies%2C%E2%80%9D%20Ziyauddin%20told%C2%A0%3Cem%3ESouth%20First%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20professor%20also%20pointed%20out%20that%20the%20state%E2%80%99s%20support%20system%20was%20regarded%20relatively%20better%20among%20its%20southern%20counterparts.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWhether%20it%E2%80%99s%20entrepreneurship%2C%20independent%20employment%2C%20or%20skill-based%20works%2C%20the%20opportunities%20are%20more%20there%20in%20general%20as%20a%20result%20of%20which%20consciousness%20among%20Muslim%20communities%20is%20also%20more.%20Teaching%20children%20is%20kind%20of%20an%20aspiration%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20explained.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20for%20greater%20female%20enrolment%20to%20higher%20education%20among%20Muslims%2C%20Ziyauddin%20remarked%20that%20men%20usually%20carry%20the%20burden%20of%20running%20the%20family%20after%20secondary%20education%2C%20due%20to%20which%20they%20have%20to%20discontinue%20their%20studies.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CFamilies%20believe%20it%20is%20good%20for%20women%20to%20study%20as%20men%20have%20the%20burden%20of%20running%20the%20family%20while%20women%20usually%20do%20not.%20However%2C%20how%20many%20of%20them%20are%20employed%20is%20another%20question%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EImtiaz%20Ahmad%2C%20a%20sociology%20professor%20at%20Delhi%E2%80%99s%20Jamia%20Milia%20Islamia%20University%2C%20said%20the%20southern%20states%20were%20more%20tolerant%20and%20inclusive%20towards%20minority%20communities.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20community%20feels%20more%20safety%20there%20as%20the%20societies%20are%20inclusive.%20The%20internal%20composition%20of%20societies%20are%20balanced.%20If%20you%20see%2C%20most%20of%20the%20conflicts%20take%20lace%20in%20Hindi%20belt%20region.%20The%20political%20environment%20in%20Hindi%20belt%20is%20a%20crucial%20reason.%20It%20is%20possible%20that%20minorties%20people%20are%20worried%20about%20safety%20of%20life%20so%20they%20think%20what%20will%20happen%20even%20after%20higher%20studies%20studying%20and%20opt%20to%20run%20family%20business%20or%20do%20odd%20jobs.%20As%20a%20result%2C%20they%20opt%20out%20of%20higher%20education%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20professor%20told%C2%A0%3Cem%3ESouth%20First%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EOther%20concerns%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EZiyauddin%20also%20raised%20concerns%20about%20the%20financial%20exclusion%20of%20the%20community%20across%20the%20country%20as%20a%20result%20of%20overall%20low%20GER%20in%20higher%20studies.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIn%20India%2C%20banks%20don%E2%80%99t%20support%20the%20Muslim%20community%20much%20as%20they%20don%E2%80%99t%20give%20credit%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20claimed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20majority%20of%20Muslims%20%5Bin%20India%5D%20belong%20to%20lower-income%20groups%20and%20don%E2%80%99t%20have%20much%20by%20way%20of%20assets.%20Their%20concern%20is%20more%20towards%20survival%20following%20more%20hands%20more%20earning%20rule.%20Due%20to%20this%2C%20the%20enrollment%20in%20higher%20studies%20is%20down%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECiting%20the%20G%20Sudhir%20Commission%E2%80%99s%202016%20report%2C%20which%20dwelt%20on%20the%20socio-economic%20and%20educational%20conditions%20of%20Muslims%20in%20Telangana%2C%20he%20said%20banks%20hesitating%20to%20provide%20financial%20aid%20to%20Muslims%20aspiring%20higher%20education%20multiplied%20their%20backwardness.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWhile%20people%20in%20lower-income%20groups%20should%20actually%20be%20the%20ones%20who%20needs%20to%20be%20supported%20through%20public%20schemes%2C%20that%20does%20not%20appear%20to%20be%20the%20case.%20It%20is%20mentioned%20in%20policy%2C%20but%20does%20not%20appear%20in%20implementation.%20It%20was%20pointed%20out%20in%20the%20reports%20of%20the%20Sudhir%20Commission%20and%20the%20Sachchar%20Committee%2C%E2%80%9D%20noted%20Ziyauddin.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20added%20that%20private%20educational%20institutions%20were%20on%20the%20rise%20in%20the%20southern%20states%20%E2%80%93%20particularly%20in%20Karnataka%2C%20Kerala%2C%20and%20Telangana.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F04160908%2FMuslim-Students-Drop-Out-Rate-at-Secondary-Level-in-Southern-states-and-Hindi-heartland-states.jpeg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F04160908%2FMuslim-Students-Drop-Out-Rate-at-Secondary-Level-in-Southern-states-and-Hindi-heartland-states.jpeg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F04160908%2FMuslim-Students-Drop-Out-Rate-at-Secondary-Level-in-Southern-states-and-Hindi-heartland-states-300x183.jpeg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F04160908%2FMuslim-Students-Drop-Out-Rate-at-Secondary-Level-in-Southern-states-and-Hindi-heartland-states-1024x625.jpeg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-700062%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22733%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CBut%20most%20Muslims%20belong%20to%20the%20lower-middle%20class%20or%20even%20below%2C%20and%20cannot%20get%20their%20children%20educated%20in%20private%20institutes.%20That%20is%20why%20they%20opt%20for%20public%20ones.%20But%20when%20they%20do%20not%20get%20admission%20there%2C%20they%20drop%20out.%20This%20is%20why%20you%20see%20an%20increase%20in%20dropouts%20after%20primary%20education%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20the%20professor.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20study%2C%20Andhra%20Pradesh%20witnessed%20the%20highest%20rate%20of%20Muslim%20students%20dropping%20out%20after%20secondary%20education%20ahead%20of%20Karnataka%20and%20Kerala.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAmong%20the%20Hindi%20heartland%20states%2C%20Bihar%20and%20Jharkhand%20were%20the%20only%20two%20states%20to%20record%20over%2020%20percent%20school%20dropouts.%20They%20were%20followed%20by%20Rajasthan%2C%20Haryana%2C%20and%20Uttar%20Pradesh%2C%20respectively.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EZiyauddin%20noted%20that%20this%20was%20a%20signal%20for%20the%20states%20to%20intervene%20in%20such%20situations%20and%20frame%20policies%20accordingly.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202022%2C%20the%20Union%20government%20decided%20to%20scrap%20the%20Maulana%20Azad%20National%20Fellowship%20(MANF)%20%E2%80%93%20aimed%20at%20minority%20students%20%E2%80%93%20from%20the%202022-23%20academic%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUnion%20Minority%20Affairs%20Minister%20Smriti%20Irani%20informed%20Parliament%20that%20the%20scheme%20would%20be%20stopped%20as%20it%20overlapped%20with%20other%20%E2%80%93%20and%20similar%20%E2%80%93%20scholarships.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESpeaking%20about%20the%20MANF%2C%20he%20said%3A%20%E2%80%9CIt%20was%20the%20last%20nail%20in%20the%20coffin.%20The%20data%20seen%20before%20and%20after%20its%20launch%20saw%20a%20better%20enrolment%20ratio%20as%20students%20registered%20due%20to%20fellowship.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ERecommendations%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20study%2C%20the%20barriers%20preventing%20Muslim%20students%20from%20pursuing%20higher%20education%20could%20include%20financial%20constraints%2C%20limited%20access%20to%20quality%20education%2C%20and%20societal%20and%20cultural%20factors.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20added%20that%20offering%20financial%20support%20to%20economically-disadvantaged%20Muslim%20students%20would%20help%20alleviate%20the%20financial%20burden%20associated%20with%20higher%20education.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EScholarships%2C%20grants%2C%20and%20educational%20loans%20tailored%20to%20the%20needs%20of%20Muslim%20students%20could%20encourage%20them%20to%20pursue%20higher%20studies.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20also%20suggested%20that%20increasing%20the%20number%20of%20scholarships%20and%20grants%20explicitly%20targeting%20Muslim%20students%20would%20incentivise%20and%20enable%20them%20to%20access%20higher%20education.%20These%20financial%20aids%20could%20make%20a%20significant%20difference%20in%20encouraging%20enrolment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20per%20the%20study%2C%20ensuring%20that%20Muslim%20students%20in%20rural%20and%20underserved%20areas%20had%20access%20to%20quality%20education%20was%20vital.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEstablishing%20more%20schools%20and%20educational%20facilities%20in%20these%20regions%20and%20improving%20their%20infrastructure%20and%20teaching%20standards%20could%20enhance%20the%20likelihood%20of%20students%20progressing%20to%20higher%20education%2C%20it%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthesouthfirst.com%2Fpolitics%2Fin-charts-southern-states-outperform-hindi-heartland-in-muslim-higher-education-enrolment-but-why%2F%5C%22%3Earticle%3C%2Fa%3E%20first%20appeared%20on%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthesouthfirst.com%2F%5C%22%3ESouth%20First%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1709551152000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F02%2F08140805%2FPhoto-4.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feducation%2Fmuslim-higher-education-enrolment-southern-states-outperform-hindi-heartland-says-study%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20'State%20of%20Muslim%20Education%20in%20India'%20study%20is%20compiled%20and%20analysed%20by%20former%20professor%20Arun%20C%20Mehta%2C%20based%20on%20data%20from%20Unified%20District%20Information%20System%20for%20Education%20Plus%2C%20and%20All%20India%20Survey%20on%20Higher%20Education.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feducation%2Fmuslim-higher-education-enrolment-southern-states-outperform-hindi-heartland-says-study%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Throwing%20Away%20Old%20Phones%3F%202%20Friends%20Earn%20Rs%20200%20Crore%20in%20Revenues%20by%20Recycling%20Them%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EThere%E2%80%99s%20a%20new%20smartphone%20being%20launched%20almost%20every%20month.%20It%20feels%20like%20the%20next%20iteration%20of%20your%20current%20phone%20hits%20the%20market%20within%20a%20year%20of%20your%20purchase.%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F309155%2Fthings-to-know-about-iit-madras-mobile-operating-system-bharos-key-features%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPhone%20companies%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20marketplaces%20tantalise%20you%20with%20enticing%20exchange%20offers%2C%20tempting%20you%20to%20upgrade.%20But%20have%20you%20ever%20paused%20to%20consider%20what%20becomes%20of%20your%20old%20phones%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMany%20marketplaces%20and%20stores%20provide%20the%20option%20of%20purchasing%20a%20refurbished%20phone.%20Such%20a%20phone%20undergoes%20thorough%20inspection%20for%20defects%2C%20repairs%2C%20and%20replacement%20of%20faulty%20parts.%20According%20to%20a%20report%20by%20%3Cem%3ERedseer%20Strategy%20Consultants%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20the%20refurbished%20or%20used%20smartphone%20market%20in%20India%20is%20projected%20to%20soar%20to%20%2410%20billion%20by%202026.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202015%2C%20Avneet%20Singh%20set%20out%20to%20buy%20an%20iPhone%20for%20his%20mother%20but%20found%20the%20new%20phone%E2%80%99s%20price%20beyond%20his%20budget%20when%20he%20visited%20a%20store%20with%20his%20friend%2C%20Saket%20Saurav.%20However%2C%20an%20enterprising%20salesman%20offered%20them%20a%20second-hand%20phone%20at%20a%20significantly%20lower%20price%2C%20nearly%20Rs%2035%2C000%20less%20than%20a%20new%20one.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDespite%20the%20tempting%20offer%2C%20the%20phone%20lacked%20any%20checks%20and%20came%20without%20a%20warranty.%20Opting%20against%20the%20risky%20purchase%2C%20Avneet%20was%20inspired%20by%20the%20experience.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWorking%20together%20at%20Shopclues%2C%20he%20and%20Saket%20recognised%20a%20problem%20worth%20solving.%20Subsequently%2C%20Shopclues%20introduced%20a%20refurbished%20mobile%20category%2C%20ReNew%2C%20which%20quickly%20generated%20multi-crore%20revenue%20within%20its%20first%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThey%20did%20extensive%20research%20on%20the%20refurbished%20mobile%20market%20and%20spotting%20an%20opportune%20time%20in%20May%202017%2C%20they%20quit%20their%20jobs%20and%20launched%20ReFit%20Global%20%E2%80%94%20a%20refurbished%20phone%20startup%2C%20on%20a%20mission%20to%20reduce%20e-waste%20by%20recycling%20and%20refurbishing%20second-hand%20gadgets.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EReFit%20is%20on%20track%20to%20achieve%20a%20revenue%20of%20Rs%20240%20crore%20this%20financial%20year%20and%20prevent%2055%2C000%20to%2065%2C000%20phones%20from%20becoming%20e-waste%20every%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3ERecycling%20e-waste%2C%20promoting%20a%20circular%20economy%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201080px)%20100vw%2C%201080px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2Frefit2-1709213840.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221080%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22ReFit%20bagged%20a%20Rs%202%20crore%20deal%20at%20Shark%20Tank%20India%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2Frefit2-1709213840.jpg%201080w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2Frefit2-1709213840-300x230.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2Frefit2-1709213840-500x383.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2Frefit2-1709213840-768x589.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2Frefit2-1709213840-150x115.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-343577%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22828%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EReFit%20bagged%20a%20Rs%202%20crore%20deal%20at%20Shark%20Tank%20India.%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20two%20Delhiites%20met%20through%20common%20friends%20and%20their%20friendship%20solidified%20after%20two%20sales%20stints%20together%20at%20LG%20and%20Shopclues.%20The%20aforementioned%20incident%20and%20subsequent%20launch%20of%20the%20ReNew%20portfolio%20at%20Shopclues%20alerted%20the%20two%20MBA%20graduates%20about%20the%20potential%20of%20the%20refurbished%20market.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThey%20conducted%20market%20research%20and%2C%20while%20overseeing%20the%20ReNew%20portfolio%2C%20gained%20practical%20insights%20into%20the%20details%20of%20the%20category.%20They%20learned%20firsthand%20about%20sourcing%20inventory%2C%20refurbishing%20phones%2C%20and%20identifying%20potential%20sales%20channels.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EComing%20from%20service-class%20backgrounds%2C%20the%20duo%20had%20long-held%20aspirations%20of%20becoming%20entrepreneurs.%20Recognising%20a%20promising%20business%20opportunity%20and%20observing%20a%20significant%20market%20gap%2C%20they%20made%20the%20bold%20decision%20to%20pursue%20their%20dreams.%20They%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F342247%2Fmangaluru-man-quits-corporate-career-for-farming-exotic-fruits-vegetables-earns-lakhs%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eleft%20behind%20their%20stable%20corporate%20careers%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20dive%20headfirst%20into%20the%20world%20of%20entrepreneurship.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThey%20invested%20all%20their%20savings%20and%20the%20then%2028-year-olds%20took%20a%20personal%20loan%20of%20Rs%2015%20lakh%20each%20and%20bootstrapped%20their%20business.%20With%20a%20total%20capital%20of%20Rs%2055%20lakh%2C%20they%20started%20ReFit%20Global%20in%20May%202017.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20refurbished%20market%20was%20just%20picking%20up%20at%20that%20time.%20Up%20until%20then%2C%20we%20only%20had%20the%20option%20to%20buy%20new%20phones%20or%20second-hand%20phones.%20A%20second-hand%20phone%20didn%E2%80%99t%20have%20credibility.%20So%20we%20decided%20to%20offer%20quality%20checked%20and%20tested%20refurbished%20phones%2C%E2%80%9D%20explains%20Saket%20(35)%2C%20co-founder%20and%20CEO%2C%20ReFit%20Global%2C%20to%20%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Better%20India.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Delhi-based%20company%20was%20started%20with%20a%20team%20of%20seven%20including%20the%20two%20founders%2C%20and%20focused%20on%20the%20offline%20market.%20Initially%2C%20Saket%20and%20Avneet%20would%20load%20about%20100%20refurbished%20phones%20in%20their%20cars%2C%20set%20out%20to%20the%20market%2C%20and%20convince%20channel%20partners%20to%20buy%20these%20phones.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20would%20visit%20different%20markets%20and%20be%20on%20the%20road%20for%20almost%2010%20days%20at%20a%20time%20in%20the%20initial%20days.%20We%20explained%20the%20product%20to%20the%20channel%20partners%20and%20asked%20them%20to%20trust%20us%20with%20a%20small%20amount%20of%20money.%20Educating%20consumers%20and%20partners%20was%20the%20first%2C%20challenging%20step%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Avneet%20(35)%2C%20co-founder%20and%20COO%2C%20ReFit%20Global.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThey%20slowly%20found%20a%20few%20channel%20partners%20who%20invested%20anywhere%20between%20Rs%202%20to%205%20lakh%2C%20which%20kicked%20off%20the%20business%20of%20the%20enterprise.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20first%20two%20years%20were%20a%20whirlwind%20of%20sleepless%20nights%20for%20these%20entrepreneurs%2C%20fully%20committed%20to%20their%20venture.%20Saket%20remembers%20that%20at%20the%20start%20of%20their%20business%2C%20his%20wife%20was%20pregnant%2C%20while%20Avneet%E2%80%99s%20parents%20had%20just%20begun%20searching%20for%20a%20bride%20for%20him.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20invested%20all%20our%20savings%3B%20it%20was%20%E2%80%98do%20or%20die%E2%80%99%20for%20us.%20We%20had%20a%20strong%20belief%20that%20it%20would%20work%2C%20and%20worked%20hard.%20We%20took%20no%20days%20off%20and%20burnt%20the%20midnight%20oil.%20We%20focused%20on%20building%20a%20good%20offline%20base%20and%20educating%20our%20distributors%20while%20building%20partnerships%20with%20mobile%20brands%20and%20marketplaces%20to%20buy%20back%20old%20phones%2C%E2%80%9D%20adds%20Saket.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETheir%20efforts%20paid%20off%20as%20people%20started%20trusting%20their%20brand%20and%20their%20sales%20grew.%20In%20the%20first%20year%20of%20operations%2C%20they%20earned%20a%20revenue%20of%20Rs%208%20crore.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EA%2047-point%20quality%20check%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2Frefit-1709539888.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20phones%20go%20throw%20a%2047%20point%20quality%20check%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2Frefit-1709539888.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2Frefit-1709539888-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2Frefit-1709539888-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2Frefit-1709539888-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2Frefit-1709539888-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-343779%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EThe%20phones%20go%20through%20a%2047-point%20quality%20check.%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EReFit%20sources%20old%20phones%20from%20three%20channels%20%E2%80%94%20marketplaces%20like%20Amazon%20and%20Flipkart%2C%C2%A0%20mobile%20manufacturers%20like%20Samsung%2C%20Oppo%2C%20Vivo%2C%20and%20Apple%2C%20and%20large%20format%20retailers%20like%20Sangeetha%2C%20Poorvika%2C%20and%20Croma.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOnce%20the%20phones%20reach%20their%20office%2C%20they%20are%20tested%20using%20ReFit%E2%80%99s%20in-house%20diagnostic%20application%20which%20has%2047%20quality%20check%20parameters.%20Saket%20says%20that%20within%20two%20and%20a%20half%20minutes%2C%20the%20application%20identifies%20what%E2%80%99s%20wrong%20with%20the%20phone.%20Their%20engineers%20then%20rectify%20and%20repair%20the%20phones%2C%20conducting%20further%20checks%20to%20see%20if%20the%20sensors%20and%20cameras%20are%20working%20properly.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOnce%20the%20faults%20are%20fixed%2C%20the%20application%20is%20run%20again%20to%20check%20if%20it%20passes%20all%20quality%20checks.%20It%20is%20then%20sent%20either%20to%20offline%20partners%20or%20sold%20through%20their%20own%20website%2C%20which%20was%20launched%20in%20October%202023.%20They%20also%20offer%20a%20six-month%20warranty%20on%20their%20phones.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETheir%20average%20selling%20price%20offline%20is%20Rs%206%2C000%20and%20online%20is%20Rs%2011%2C000.%20There%20is%20more%20demand%20for%20high-end%20phones%20online%2C%20say%20the%20founders.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThey%20further%20share%20that%20they%20sell%20between%2055%2C000%20to%2065%2C000%20phones%20every%20month%20and%20have%20sold%20over%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F263287%2Fbangalore-global-childrens-peace-award-photograph-kids-mobile-parents%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%201.75%20million%20phones%20%3C%2Fa%3Eto%20date.%20They%20claim%20that%20they%E2%80%99ve%20been%20profitable%20from%20the%20outset%20and%20have%20achieved%20a%20consistent%20100%20percent%20year-on-year%20growth.%20Their%20revenue%20reached%20Rs%20187%20crore%20last%20year%20and%20is%20projected%20to%20hit%20Rs%20240%20crore%20this%20year.%20Operating%20in%20over%20100%20cities%2C%20they%20have%20a%20network%20of%20more%20than%2050%2C000%20retailers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20major%20difference%20between%20a%20second-hand%20and%20refurbished%20phone%2C%20explains%20Saket%2C%20is%20the%20quality%20and%20credibility.%20%E2%80%9CThere%20is%20no%20quality%20testing%20or%20checking%20done%20on%20a%20second-hand%20phone.%20We%20ensure%20that%20there%20is%20no%20problem%20with%20the%20phone%20and%20give%20you%20a%20warranty%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20phones%20are%20also%20beneficial%20for%20the%20environment%20as%20they%20extend%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F252476%2Fmumbai-e-waste-recycling-discard-dead-laptops-mobile-phones-computer-keyboard-ecoreco-book-my-junk-environment-india-nor41%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elifespan%20of%20gadgets%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20prevent%20them%20from%20contributing%20to%20waste.%20In%202022%2C%20the%20Waste%20Electrical%20and%20Electronic%20Equipment%20(WEEE)%20forum%20reported%20that%205.3%20billion%20mobile%20phones%20would%20become%20waste%20in%20that%20year%20alone.%20Instead%20of%20recycling%20old%20phones%2C%20many%20people%20either%20keep%20them%20at%20home%20or%20discard%20them%20in%20bins.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20these%20devices%20contain%20valuable%20materials%20like%20gold%2C%20copper%2C%20and%20silver%2C%20which%2C%20if%20recycled%2C%20can%20prevent%20the%20need%20for%20extracting%20precious%20minerals%20and%20help%20reduce%20carbon%20emissions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EReFit%20also%20appeared%20on%20Shark%20Tank%20India%20Season%203%20and%20secured%20a%20deal%20for%20Rs%202%20crore%20from%20three%20%E2%80%98Sharks%E2%80%99%20%E2%80%94%20Anupam%20Mittal%2C%20Vineeta%20Singh%2C%20and%20Amit%20Jain.%20Post%20their%20appearance%20on%20Shark%20Tank%2C%20they%20have%20received%20over%2020%2C000%20queries%20from%20retailers%20and%20distributors%20in%20just%2010%20days%2C%20say%20the%20elated%20founders%2C%20adding%20that%20they%20want%20to%20increase%20their%20online%20presence%20in%20the%20coming%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFrom%20initially%20keeping%20their%20venture%20a%20secret%20from%20their%20families%20to%20establishing%20a%20company%20valued%20at%20Rs%20200%20crore%2C%20Avneet%20and%20Saket%20exemplify%20the%20power%20of%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F340982%2Fiit-delhi-graduates-aroleap-x-fitness-home-gym-smart-ai-strength-training-equipment-innovation%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehard%20work%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20seizing%20opportunities%20at%20the%20right%20time%2C%20and%20embodying%20the%20hustle%20culture.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CYou%20need%20to%20be%20honest%20with%20yourself%20and%20your%20customers%2C%20work%20hard%2C%20and%20have%20the%20zeal%20to%20build%20a%20business.%20Don%E2%80%99t%20stick%20to%20a%20strategy%3B%20instead%2C%20be%20willing%20to%20redo%20things%20if%20something%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20work.%20We%20achieved%20our%20goals%20because%20our%20intent%20and%20passion%20were%20strong%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Avneet.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EEdited%20by%20Pranita%20Bhat%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch5%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3ESources%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fh5%3E%5Cn%3Ch5%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fweee-forum.org%2Fws_news%2Fof-16-billion-mobile-phones-possessed-worldwide-5-3-billion-will-become-waste-in-2022%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EWEEE%20Forum%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fh5%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1709550423000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2Frefit2-1709213840.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F%3Fp%3D343568%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Delhi-based%20Avneet%20Singh%20and%20Saket%20Saurav%20founded%20ReFit%20Global%20in%202017.%20Through%20a%20meticulous%2047-point%20quality%20check%2C%20they%20ensure%20the%20reliability%20of%20their%20refurbished%20phones%2C%20selling%20over%201.75%20million%20units%20to%20date%20and%20projecting%20a%20revenue%20of%20Rs%20240%20crore%20for%20the%20current%20year.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22Sowmya%20Mani%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F343568%2Fbuy-refurbished-second-hand-mobile-phone-refit-global-delhi-avneet-singh-saket-saurav-shark-tank%2F%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Four%20astronauts%20blast%20off%20to%20International%20Space%20Station%20for%20six-month%20stay%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1709549400000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fe3.365dm.com%2F24%2F03%2F768x432%2Fskynews-iss-spacex_6478037.jpg%3F20240304095701%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Ffour-astronauts-blast-off-to-international-space-station-on-spacex-rocket-13087015%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Four%20astronauts%20have%20blasted%20off%20to%20the%20International%20Space%20Station%20for%20a%20six-month%20stint%20in%20orbit.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A103%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Ffour-astronauts-blast-off-to-international-space-station-on-spacex-rocket-13087015%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Lakhimpur-Kheri%20Violence%3A%20Farmers%20Livid%20Over%20'Conspirator'%20Teni's%20Name%20on%20BJP's%20LS%20Candidate%20List%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F04154105%2FUntitled-design-24-1.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ELucknow%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Farmers%20have%20strongly%20objected%20to%20the%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%E2%80%99s%20(BJP)%20candidature%20of%20Ajay%20Mishra%20%E2%80%9CTeni%E2%80%9D%20for%20the%20Lakhimpur-Kheri%20parliamentary%20seat%20in%20Uttar%20Pradesh.%20The%20farmer%20leaders%2C%20demanding%20Teni%E2%80%99s%20resignation%20since%20the%20horrific%20Lakhimpur-Kheri%202021%20incident%2C%20were%20stunned%20to%20see%20Teni%E2%80%99s%20name%20included%20in%20the%20first%20list%20of%20BJP%20candidates%20for%20the%20upcoming%20general%20elections.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20the%20BJP%20announced%20Teni%E2%80%99s%20candidature%2C%20annoyed%20farmer%20leaders%20reacted%20by%20saying%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20BJP%20has%20sprinkled%20salt%20on%20our%20wounds.%E2%80%9D%20They%20decided%20to%20oppose%20the%20BJP%20and%20Teni%20both%20in%20the%20general%20election%20and%20call%20the%20BJP%20%E2%80%9Cpro-corporate%2C%20anti-farmers.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20March%203%20in%20New%20Delhi%2C%20the%20BJP%20released%20the%20names%20of%20195%20candidates%20from%2016%20states%20and%20two%20Union%20territories.%20Teni%20is%20a%20junior%20minister%20in%20the%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi-led%20Union%20government%E2%80%99s%20home%20department.%20Junior%20minister%E2%80%99s%20son%2C%20Ashish%20Mishra%2C%20is%20charged%20with%20being%20involved%20in%20the%20Lakhimpur%20Kheri%20incident%2C%20which%20claimed%20the%20lives%20of%20four%20farmers%20and%20a%20journalist.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESanyukt%20Kisan%20Morcha%20(SKM)%2C%20an%20umbrella%20body%20of%20several%20farmer%20unions%2C%20believes%20two-term%20parliamentarian%20Teni%20was%20a%20conspirator%20in%20the%20Lakhimpur-Kheri%20incident%20and%20has%20been%20putting%20pressure%20on%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20and%20his%20government%20for%20Teni%E2%80%99s%20resignation%20from%20the%20Council%20of%20Ministers%20for%20the%20past%20two%20years.%20The%20demand%20for%20his%20resignation%20is%20also%20part%20of%20the%20ongoing%20farmer%20protest%20on%20the%20outskirts%20of%20the%20national%20capital%2C%20Delhi.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Flakhimpur-kheri-bjp-ashish-mishra-rule-of-law%5C%22%3EIn%20Lakhimpur%20Kheri%2C%20BJP%20Proves%20India%20Has%20No%20Rule%20of%20Law%20Today%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIrked%20farmer%20leaders%20demanded%20that%20the%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20top%20brass%20withdraw%20Teni%E2%80%99s%20candidature%20or%20face%20the%20consequences%20of%20betraying%20farmers%20in%20the%20next%20elections.%20According%20to%20Ashish%20Mittal%2C%20executive%20member%20of%20the%20SKM%20coordination%20committee%2C%20%E2%80%9CNow%20it%20is%20clear%20that%20under%20the%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20rule%2C%20alleged%20criminals%20like%20Teni%20and%20Brij%20Bhushan%20Sharan%20Singh%20thrive%20while%20poor%20students%2C%20women%2C%20labourers%2C%20and%20farmers%20face%20state-sponsored%20repression.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMittal%20is%20concerned%20about%20the%20future%20of%20democracy%20in%20the%20country%2C%20saying%2C%20%E2%80%9CBy%20giving%20a%20ticket%20to%20Teni%2C%20the%20BJP%20has%20sent%20a%20loud%20and%20clear%20message%20that%20if%20it%20retains%20power%20in%202024%2C%20it%20will%20crush%20all%20democratic%20movements.%E2%80%9D%20Mittal%2C%20who%20is%20also%20the%20general%20secretary%20of%20the%20Akhil%20Bharatiya%20Kisan%20Mazdoor%20Sabha%2C%20is%20accusing%20the%20BJP%20government%20of%20hypocrisy%20for%20honouring%20the%20pro-farmer%20agronomist%20M.S.%20Swaminathan%20with%20the%20Bharat%20Ratan%20award%20while%20also%20supporting%20a%20candidate%20responsible%20for%20the%20deaths%20of%20farmers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnother%20farmer%20leader%2C%20Mukut%20Singh%2C%20the%20national%20joint%20secretary%20of%20All%20India%20Kisan%20Sabha%2C%20told%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%20that%20farmers%20will%20not%20retreat%20from%20their%20demand%20at%20any%20cost%20to%20register%20a%20first%20information%20report%20against%20Teni%20in%20the%20Lakhimpur-Kheri%20case%20under%20Section%20120-B%20(Criminal%20Conspiracy)%20of%20the%20Indian%20Penal%20Code.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDespite%20the%20numerous%20nationwide%20protests%20organised%20by%20farmers%20against%20Teni%2C%20Singh%20continued%2C%20%E2%80%9CHis%20candidacy%20exemplifies%20the%20anti-democratic%20stance%20of%20the%20BJP.%E2%80%9D%20The%20farmer%20leader%20continued%20by%20stating%20that%20the%20SKM%20will%20urge%20the%20nation%E2%80%99s%20farmers%20to%20vote%20against%20the%20anti-farmer%20BJP%20in%20the%20forthcoming%20elections.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20tragic%20reminiscence%20of%20the%20Lakhimpur%20incident%20remains%20alive%20in%20our%20hearts.%20The%20BJP%20hurt%20the%20farmer%E2%80%99s%20sentiments%20by%20giving%20tickets%20to%20Teni%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20K.%20Krishnaprasad%2C%20AKIS%E2%80%99%20finance%20secretary.%20When%20questioned%20about%20the%20political%20impacts%20of%20Teni%E2%80%99s%20candidature%2C%20farmer%20leader%20K.%20Krishnaprasad%20stated%20that%20farmers%20all%20over%20the%20nation%2C%20not%20just%20in%20Uttar%20Pradesh%2C%20are%20furious%20with%20the%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20decision%20%E2%80%93%20now%20farmers%20are%20overthrowing%20this%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20arrogant%20government%20in%20the%20next%20election.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELocal%20farmers%20of%20Lakhimpur-Kheri%20are%20also%20upset%20and%20want%20the%20BJP%20to%20reconsider%20its%20decision.%20Following%20the%20release%20of%20the%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20candidate%20list%2C%20a%20meeting%20of%20the%20Bharatiya%20Kisaan%20Union%20was%20convened%2C%20according%20to%20Dilbhag%20Singh%20%E2%80%9CSindhu%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20district%20president%20of%20the%20union.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFarmers%20protested%20Teni%E2%80%99s%20candidature%20and%20demanded%20that%20Modi%20replace%20him%20with%20another%20candidate.%20%E2%80%9CAstonishingly%2C%20a%20man%20who%20should%20be%20imprisoned%20for%20his%20heinous%20conspiracy%20against%20farmers%20is%20going%20to%20contest%20for%20office%20on%20the%20symbol%20of%20the%20ruling%20party%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20disgruntled%20farmer%20leader%20Sindhu.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIshwari%20Prasad%20Kushwaha%2C%20secretary%20of%20Kisaan%20Mahasabha%20(Tikait)%2C%20views%20the%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20decision%20to%20field%20Teni%20from%20Lakimpur-Kheri%20as%20mocking%20crores%20of%20Indian%20farmers%2C%20while%20they%20persist%20in%20demanding%20his%20resignation.%20According%20to%20him%2C%20farmers%20are%20angry%20with%20the%20BJP%2C%20and%20they%20plan%20to%20raise%20the%20Lakhimpur-Kheri%20issue%20at%20the%20Mahapanchayat%20on%20March%2014%20at%20Ramlila%20Ground%20in%20Delhi.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CBJP%20promised%20to%20double%20the%20farmers%E2%80%99%20income%20in%202014%2C%20but%20after%20getting%20power%2C%20put%20the%20farmer%E2%80%99s%20issues%20like%20the%20demand%20of%20MSP%2C%20etc.%20on%20the%20back%20burner%20and%20turned%20blind%20eyes%20towards%20their%20plights%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Kushwaha.%20Anguished%20farmers%20would%20upset%20the%20apple%20cart%20of%20the%20BJP%20because%20it%20has%20been%20dancing%20to%20corporate%20tunes%20and%20repressing%20farmers%20for%20a%20decade%20since%20coming%20to%20power%20in%202014.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20to%20be%20recalled%20that%20on%20October%203%2C%202021%2C%20Teni%E2%80%99s%20son%E2%80%99s%20convoy%20allegedly%20rammed%20three%20farmers%20and%20a%20journalist%20in%20Tikunia%2C%20Lakhimpur-Kheri.%20The%20deceased%20farmers%20were%20returning%20from%20protesting%20three%20Modi%20government%20farm%20laws%20when%20the%20incident%20occurred.%20Later%20on%2C%20after%20a%20long%20and%20massive%20farmer%20protest%2C%20the%20government%20repealed%20these%20laws.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFarmers%20in%20the%20Lakimpur-Kheri%20district%20say%20that%20Teni%2C%20who%20is%20the%20minister%20of%20state%20for%20home%2C%20went%20to%20an%20event%20in%20Palia%2C%20Lakhimpur%20Kheri%20district%2C%20in%20September%202021.%20Some%20members%20of%20the%20farmer%E2%80%99s%20union%20waved%20black%20flags%20as%20a%20protest%20during%20the%20event.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20farmers%2C%20after%20this%20protest%2C%20Tani%20purportedly%20plotted%20a%20conspiracy%20to%20assassinate%20the%20farmers%20for%20protesting%20against%20the%20controversial%20farm%20laws.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETeni%20allegedly%20intimidated%20the%20protesting%20farmers%20during%20his%20speech%2C%20saying%2C%20%E2%80%9CSudhar%20jao%2C%20nahi%20toh%20hum%20sudhaar%20denge%2C%20do%20minute%20me.%E2%80%9D%20(You%20better%20change%20your%20ways%2C%20or%20we%E2%80%99ll%20teach%20you%20a%20lesson%20in%20two%20minutes.)%20Rough%20translation%20from%20Hindi.%20A%20video%20of%20his%20speech%20went%20viral%20following%20the%20Lakimpur-Kheri%20incident.%20Farmers%20accuse%20Teni%20of%20orchestrating%20a%20conspiracy%20based%20on%20his%20speech%20and%20want%20him%20to%20step%20down%20as%20minister.%20They%20also%20want%20the%20government%20to%20prosecute%20him%20for%20the%20Lakhimpur%20incident.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1709549398000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F04154105%2FUntitled-design-24-1.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Flakhimpur-kheri-v