vernment%20Permission%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20a%20fresh%20advisory%20over%20the%20weekend%2C%20minister%20Rajeev%20Chandrasekhar%20said%20on%20March%202%20that%20it%20has%20asked%20artificial%20intelligence%20platforms%20to%20seek%20its%20permission%20before%20launching%20an%20AI%20product%20in%20the%20country.%20%3Cem%3EMoneylife%3C%2Fem%3E%20reports%20that%20%E2%80%9Call%20intermediaries%20have%20been%20told%20to%20ensure%20compliance%20with%20the%20advisory%2C%20which%20was%20issued%20on%20March%201%20evening%2C%20with%20immediate%20effect%20and%20to%20submit%20an%20action%20taken-cum-status%20report%20to%20the%20ministry%20within%2015%20days.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EChandrashekhar%2C%20now%20a%20BJP%20candidate%20for%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20polls%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9Cthis%20signals%20that%20we%20are%20moving%20to%20a%20regime%20when%20a%20lot%20of%20rigour%20is%20needed%20before%20a%20product%20is%20launched.%20You%20don%E2%80%99t%20do%20that%20with%20cars%20or%20microprocessors.%20Why%20is%20that%20for%20such%20a%20transformative%20tech%20like%20AI%20there%20are%20no%20guardrails%20between%20what%20is%20in%20the%20lab%20and%20what%20goes%20out%20to%20the%20public.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20appears%20to%20signal%20a%20shift%20in%20India%E2%80%99s%20position%20on%20AI%20as%20India%20has%20repeatedly%20indicated%20it%20is%20gung-ho%20over%20it%20and%20Rajeev%20Chandrashekhar%20himself%20had%20said%2C%20days%20ago%20on%20February%2020%2C%20that%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livemint.com%2Fai%2Fartificial-intelligence%2Findia-to-come-up-with-ai-regulations-framework-by-june-july-this-year-rajeev-chandrasekhar-msde-11708409300377.html%23%3A~%3Atext%3DIndia%2520plans%2520to%2520introduce%2520the%2Cby%2520June%252DJuly%2520this%2520year.%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CIndia%20plans%20to%20introduce%20the%20first%20draft%20of%20AI%20regulations%20by%20June-July.%E2