ution.%20Such%20lawmakers%20would%20be%20immune%20from%20prosecution%20if%20they%20upheld%20their%20end%20of%20the%20bargain%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livelaw.in%2Ftop-stories%2Fsupreme-court-mps-mlas-bribe-vote-speech-legislature-claim-immunity-251136%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3ELiveLaw%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20noted%20the%20earlier%20order%20as%20having%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202012%2C%20Jharkhand%20Mukti%20Morcha%20leader%20Sita%20Soren%20was%20accused%20of%20accepting%20a%20bribe%20for%20a%20Rajya%20Sabha%20vote%20and%20claimed%20immunity%20under%20Article%20194(2).%20When%20the%20Jharkhand%20high%20court%20dismissed%20her%20plea%2C%20Soren%20challenged%20it%20in%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20which%20heard%20the%20case%20in%20October%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20judgment%20in%20%3Cem%3EPV%20Narasimha%20Rao%3C%2Fem%3E%20which%20grants%20immunity%20from%20prosecution%20to%20a%20member%20of%20a%20legislature%20who%20has%20allegedly%20engaged%20in%20bribery%20for%20casting%20a%20vote%20or%20making%20a%20speech%20has%20wide%20ramifications%20on%20public%20interest%2C%20probity%20in%20public%20life%2C%20and%20parliamentary%20democracy.%20There%20is%20a%20grave%20danger%20of%20this%20court%20allowing%20the%20error%20to%20be%20perpetuated%20if%20the%20decision%20were%20not%20reconsidered%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20bench%20said%2C%20according%20to%20%3Cem%3ELiveLaw%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20observed%20that%20it%20was%20disagreeing%20the%20overruling%20the%20earlier%20verdict.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Supreme%20Court%20also%20said%20that%20the%20offence%20of%20bribery%20under%20the%20Prevention%20of%20Corruption%20Act%20is%20%E2%80%9Ccomplete%E2%80%9D%20the%20moment%20a%20bribe%20is%20taken%20and%20cannot%20depend%20on%20whether%20the%20receiver%20makes%20good%20on%20the%20promise.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CCorruption%20and%20bribery%20of%20members%20of%20the%20legislature%20erode%20the%20foundation%20of%20Indian%20parliamentary%20democracy.%2